&ldquo;He was very good. You don&rsquo;t see van Dijk disturbed so often. He (van Dijk) was winning his headers, but he was always having to fight to win them. He was put under big pressure and Rondon was a big problem, especially for Lovren.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;Rondon is so often found up front isolated on his own in this Newcastle team. The wide players, Ayoze and Atsu go back in and Rondon has to fight on his own. He has to wait for people to support him. But he still holds it up and brings people into play. Tonight he was really good.&rdquo;
